    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese figurative sculpture construction technique characteristic of the early Heian period (794-1185) where the head and torso were carved from the same block of wood. The arms, legs and other elements such as drapery were many times carved from separate pieces of wood and attached.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
